🚀 Professional Header

BTC EMA Trend Strategy V5 PRO is a trend-following strategy designed to identify strong directional moves in the cryptocurrency market using a combination of EMAs, volatility filters, market structure, and momentum confirmation.

The strategy automatically detects LONG and SHORT opportunities, visualizes risk and reward zones, and displays performance statistics directly on the chart.

📊 Strategy Logic

The system uses four exponential moving averages to identify market trend:

• EMA 20 – short-term momentum
• EMA 50 – short-term trend
• EMA 100 – medium-term trend
• EMA 200 – long-term trend filter

Trades are taken only when price aligns with the dominant trend.

⚡ Momentum Confirmation (CISD)

The strategy includes a CISD (Candle Impulse Structure Detection) filter that detects strong momentum candles.

When a large impulse candle breaks the previous high or low with a significantly larger body, the script highlights the area using CISD boxes, signaling potential institutional momentum.

📈 Entry Conditions
LONG

A long trade is opened when:

• EMA20 is above EMA50
• Price is above EMA200
• Price retests EMA20
• ADX confirms strong trend
• Market volatility is above average

SHORT

A short trade is opened when:

• EMA20 is below EMA50
• Price is below EMA200
• Price retests EMA20 from below
• ADX confirms strong trend
• Market volatility is above average

🎯 Risk Management

The strategy uses ATR-based dynamic Stop Loss and a 3:1 Risk-to-Reward ratio.

Each trade is displayed with visual trade boxes:

🟩 Green zone → potential profit
🟥 Red zone → risk area

📊 Dashboard

A built-in dashboard displays key strategy statistics:

• Net Profit
• Total Trades
• Win Rate
• Maximum Drawdown

This allows traders to quickly evaluate performance during backtesting.

🎨 Chart Features

The script includes multiple visual tools:

✔ EMA trend lines
✔ CISD momentum boxes
✔ Market structure labels (HH, HL, LH, LL)
✔ LONG / SHORT signal arrows
✔ Trade risk/reward boxes
✔ Trend heatmap based on EMA200

⚠️ Note

The strategy performs best in strong trending markets and may produce weaker results during sideways consolidation.

For optimal performance, test the strategy on 15m, 1H, or 4H timeframes.

⚠️ Disclaimer:
This AI is not a financial advisor; please consult your financial advisor for personalized advice.
